{# 
  HERO SECTION WITH DUAL BACKGROUND SLIDESHOW SYSTEM
  
  This section implements a sophisticated dual slideshow system:
  1. Full-section background slideshow covering the entire hero area
  2. Individual hero card background slideshow behind the text content
  
  The dual system creates visual depth and interest while maintaining excellent readability.
  Technical implementation uses GSAP animations with staggered timing for visual variety.
#}
<section class="relative bg-gradient-to-br from-gray-900 via-wavgen-dark-purple to-wavgen-purple min-h-screen flex items-center">
    <!-- Hero Section Background Slideshow -->
    {# 
      FULL-SECTION BACKGROUND SLIDESHOW
      
      This slideshow covers the entire hero section background with high-resolution images.
      Key features:
      - Uses collections.backgrounds from Eleventy (defined in .eleventy.js)
      - Images are positioned absolutely to cover the full section
      - First image starts visible (40% opacity), others start hidden (0% opacity)
      - GSAP animations in gallery.js handle the slideshow transitions
      - 4-second intervals create dramatic visual impact without being distracting
    #}
    <div class="hero-section-bg-slideshow absolute inset-0">
        {%- for background in collections.backgrounds %}
          {# Loop through all background images from the backgrounds collection #}
          {# Each image is positioned absolutely to cover the full section area #}
          <img src="{{ background.url }}" alt="Background" loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="hero-section-bg-slide absolute inset-0 w-full h-full object-cover transition-opacity duration-1000" style="opacity: {% if loop.first %}0.4{% else %}0{% endif %};">
          {# 
            CSS Classes Explained:
            - hero-section-bg-slide: Target class for GSAP animations in gallery.js
            - absolute inset-0: Positions image to cover entire parent container
            - w-full h-full: Ensures image fills the container dimensions
            - object-cover: Maintains aspect ratio while covering the area (like CSS background-size: cover)
            - transition-opacity duration-1000: Smooth 1-second opacity transitions
            
            Inline Style Logic:
            - First image (loop.first) starts at 40% opacity for immediate visual impact
            - All other images start at 0% opacity and will be animated by GSAP
            - 40% opacity provides dramatic effect while maintaining text readability
          #}
        {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    {# Semi-transparent overlay to enhance text readability and add visual depth #}
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-black opacity-20"></div>
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 relative z-10">
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-2 gap-12 items-center">
            <!-- Hero Content -->
            {# 
              HERO CARD WITH INDEPENDENT BACKGROUND SLIDESHOW
              
              This is the second part of the dual slideshow system - a localized slideshow
              that runs behind the hero text content. It operates independently from the
              full-section background slideshow above, creating layered visual depth.
            #}
            <div class="animate-fade-in relative">
                <!-- Hero Background Slideshow -->
                {# 
